description:
&lt;p&gt;Do you have oncology experience? Can you demonstrate effective leadership skills? do you like a challenge?&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;This is an exciting opportunity to join the chemotherapy day treatment unit at Singleton Hospital within the South West Wales Cancer Centre.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The post holder will be the unit clinical lead and will join a small but dedicated nursing team, who are responsible for delivering oral and intravenous chemotherapy. The post holder will work alongside a chemotherapy day unit manager and will deputize for her in her absence.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; English and/or Welsh speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing Date: 10/11/2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sue Rowland&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Susan.rowland@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Chemotherapy Day Unit Manager, Singleton Hospital&lt;/p&gt;
